    "This suggests that beyond a certain threshold, model size alone does not correlate with better extraction performance.",
    "Nevertheless, the models 14B qwen3, 32B deepseek-r1, and 20B gpt-oss exhibit a favourable trade-off between parameter count and alignment with human annotations.",
    "ConclusionWe introduce a new dataset of Czech and Slovak texts with fine-grained evidence annotations, produced by two independent annotators for each sample.",
    "This dataset enables the computation of inter-annotator agreement, which we measure using the Hungarian matching algorithm and the Token-F1 metric, resulting in a score of 47.",
    "Additionally, it provides a foundation for evaluating the alignment of LLM-generated evidence with human judgments -filling an existing gap in available resources.Using this dataset, we analysed the ability of various LLMs to generate valid fine-grained evidence."
